From 46fe3fc4893720a21a896af9fc483d90b162ff1f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: KITOHSY <hongsun900912@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 10:05:03 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 03/12] T13: ComputerManager connect entry point + pending
 token bookkeeping
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SmartClassroom T13 — wires the moonlight:// URL plumbing from the previous
patch into a concrete handler that auto-adds the target host and stamps
the broker-issued token/host-id onto the resulting NvComputer.

  * NvComputer gains two ephemeral fields, pendingConnectToken and
    pendingHostId. They are not in the serialize/isEqualSerialized path
    because the raw token is short-lived (expires with the reservation
    window) and writing it to QSettings on disk would leak it.

  * ComputerManager exposes requestConnect(address, port, token, hostId),
    which (a) stamps the fields directly if the host is already in
    m_KnownHosts under any of its addresses, or (b) queues the (token,
    hostId) under "ip:port" in m_PendingTokensByAddress and calls
    addNewHost(...). The existing handleComputerStateChanged path then
    drains the queue once polling resolves the new host.

  * A static stashPendingConnect() handles the bootstrap timing problem:
    main.cpp's ConnectRequested switch arm runs before QML constructs
    ComputerManager via its singleton lambda, so stash queues into a
    static list while no instance exists, and the ComputerManager
    constructor flushes the static queue onto the live instance. Once
    constructed, stashPendingConnect routes straight through.

  * main.cpp's ConnectRequested arm and the QDesktopServices URL handler
    now both feed ComputerManager::stashPendingConnect via a shared
    scT13DispatchMoonlightUrl() helper. The forwarded-URL path from the
    single-instance receiver loops through QDesktopServices::openUrl so
    it lands in the same handler.

NvHTTP Bearer header injection and PIN/cert auto-fill — what actually
gets the user to "0 inputs" — are T14 and consume these pendingConnectToken
/ pendingHostId fields from there. T13 only carries them.
